*These Feasts are optional, except in the countries 
indicated, where they are celebrated as Feasts of the 
rank of Class A. The Feasts which have octaves are 
printed in italics. 

In the British Empire it is customary to hold services 
of thanksgiving on Empire Day (May 24) and Armis- 
tice Day (November 11). 

